cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CV, cs.NE, cs.SY

The paper discusses the performance measurement of deep Bayesian neural networks, which is a topic related to machine learning and artificial intelligence. Therefore, cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) are the most likely sub-categories. Additionally, the paper mentions the use of Bayesian neural networks in computer vision (cs.CV) and control systems (cs.SY), which are also relevant sub-categories. Finally, the paper proposes metrics for measuring uncertainty divergence, which is related to neural network optimization and training, making cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) a possible sub-category as well.
